A '''common [[commercial policy]]''' is several states co-ordinateing some or all aspects of their trade policy.

It is sometimes agreed by treaty within a [[customs union]]. In the case of the [[European Union]], a form of the [[EU's common commercial policy]] has been in place since 1957.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ec.europa.eu/archives/igc2000/geninfo/fact-sheets/fact-sheet6/index_en.htm|title=Archives - Intergovernemental Conference|website=ec.europa.eu}}</ref> 

A common commercial policy is also [[Common Commercial Policy (MERCOSUR)|an aim of Mercosur]].{{cn|date=May 2018}}

